Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the development of logical entropy, which is a topic that falls under mathematical logic, specifically in the area of partition logic. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the basic notions of logical information theory, which involves the use of algorithms and data structures, falling under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the comparison of logical entropy with Shannon entropy, which is a topic that falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
